2002-05-21  rprix  <rprix@microwave>

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/sound.c:
	corrected bug with SDL_mixer checking: I had put tests before
	inclusion of <config.h>, which doesn't make much sense...

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/system.h:
	conditional inclusion of <SDL/SDL_mixer.h> only when found by configure!

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/sound.c:
	conditional compilation now takes accound of configure-defines:
	HAVE_LIBSDL_MIXER and HAVE_SDL_SDL_H. If either is missing, sound
	is "dummy-compiled", everything should work ok!.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/init.c:
	reactivated loading of Title-picture in Old engine

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/text.c:
	fixed bug in Initial Scroll-text: Text-screen is cleared before
	scrolling to avoid "smearing"

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/main.c:
	default value for global joy_sensitivity = 1.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/keyboard.c:
	added Joystick-event reading in keyboard_update(): joystick motion is
	simply mapped to Motion-keys and Space.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/joy.c:
	complete Joystick initialisation in Init_Joy().

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/init.c:
	added new switch [-j|--sensitivity=<n>] that changes analog-joystick
	sensitivity in the range [0,32].

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/global.h:
	added global joystick variables relating to joy.c

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/enemy.c:
	fixed (release-critical) bug in MoveEnemys() that produced
	endless-loop if enemy was put on a waypoint with _zero_ connections.

2002-05-21  jprix  <jprix@microwave>

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/sound.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/text.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/main.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/misc.c:
	Sound can now really be completely turned of via command line, which was incomplete.
	Corrected the bug in the scrolling text at the beginning.  Seems releasable.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/defs.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/influ.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/misc.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/svgaemu.c:
	Corrected out some damage done to the old engine while introducing new fonts.
	Reactivated palette color operations, which cuts down FPS to about 65 but
	Influs color is now always correct.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/init.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/main.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/rahmen.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/text.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/global.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c:
	Paradroid font funktioniert wieder, wenn auch noch nicht besonders schoen.

2002-05-20  jprix  <jprix@microwave>

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/blocks.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/defs.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/global.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/proto.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/rahmen.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Rahmen is displayed again, although without font.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/blocks.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/defs.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/global.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/init.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/proto.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/ship.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/text.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	the numbers in influ and enemy droid are now visible again.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/defs.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/ship.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/svgaemu.c:
	Elevator picture now visible again.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Blasts are visible again.  dirty Blast-Bullet collision check disabled.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Bullets are visible again, but bullet-bullet-collision checking remains disabled.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Influencer is now visible again with the ne, but numbers are still omittet for now.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/defs.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Enemys are visible again, although the numbers are omittet for now.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Background scrolling works fully now!
	The procedure is very abstract and very powerful in my opinion!
	All of the clipping is done via SDL and its clipping capabilities.
	I hope the SDL knows what to do and their code is really bugfree!!!
	But it seems so.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/misc.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Map now visible again with the new engine.  Movement and enemys and that
	also runs well since there were no changes to this part.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/main.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/map.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/proto.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/view.c:
	Renamed GetInternFenster into Assemble_Combat_Picture, which will do the
	assembling of the screen, but not into some internal window but rather into
	the ne_screen.  PutInternFenster will be a dumb return and updating of the
	screen can be done via SDL_Flip later.

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/init.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/rahmen.c:
	Added some more conditional compilations for the new engine.
	Deactivated the termination after InitPicutres.

2002-05-20  rprix  <rprix@microwave>

	* /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/init.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/struct.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/takeover.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/vars.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/blocks.c, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/defs.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/global.h, /local/cvsRep/FD/FreeDroid/src/graphics.c:
